<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08118</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE SCHOOL HEALTH AND SAFETY OFFICE IN EVERY PUBLIC SCHOOL IN THE COUNTRY, PROVIDING FUNDS THEREFOR, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to address the health, safety, and security issues in different schools nationwide by creating the School Health and Safety Office, defining its roles, functions, responsibilities, and accountabilities.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “School Health and Safety Act of 2018.” </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C., MACEDA, EDWARD VERA PEREZ, MARTINEZ, ERIC M., MALAPITAN, DALE &quot;ALONG&quot; R., OLIVAREZ, ERIC L.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-15</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-09-05)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-09-06)</td><tr><td>3. Calixto-Rubiano (000 2018-09-19)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2018-08-28</td></tr></table>